sailpoint.object
Class GridState

java.lang.Object
  sailpoint.tools.xml.AbstractXmlObject
      sailpoint.object.GridState
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, org.json.JSONString, sailpoint.tools.xml.PersistentXmlObject
public class GridState
extends AbstractXmlObject
implements org.json.JSONString

A GridState holds information about how a grid should be displayed. This is used when transitioning in the UI to remember how a grid was previously displayed so you can go back to the same row in the grid, use the same sorting, etc... This is used in conjunction with the SailPoint.GridState javascript object by converting this object to JSON and passing the JSON-created object to the SailPoint.GridState.
